{"/service/ndnp/kyu/batch_kyu_mastiff_ver02/data/sn86069021/00516997631/1910093001/0776.xml":{"full_text":"lOONAL roJo\u00ae b\nHEN you taka la lb city of Wash\nlagtoa what tha unregenerato call\na \"rubber-nick wagon\" your eoona\nla bouad to lead by tha Coarnoa\ndub Uatll tha Metropolitan dub\nbuilt It sew quartan Ita build\nlag wu dtuatad Bear that which\nhouses tha Coamoa members It\nfonaatioa giver oa the alghtaaa\nlng automobile to declare to tha\npusengera that the Metropolitan\nclub \"which you nee oa your right\nla the home of tha Lobe gad\ntba Coamoa dub which you aea oa\nyour loft la the homo of tha cranka\"\nPresumably adentlata have\ntomed to being dubbed cranka by tha unthinking\nIt baa beon a long hard struggle at tiinaa tor\nsome adentlata to get recognition from tha world\nTha Coamoa dub baa a membership which in\ncludes soma of tba greatest adentlata of tha\nUnited States and in its ncn-resldent member\nship soma of tha greatest scientists of tha world\nThors are botanists astronomers ornitholo\ngists and In fad scientists of all kinds and de\nscriptions to bo found nightly in tha 'great\nsweeping parlors of the club\u2019s quarters Thera la\nJust as much hospitality and Jollity In tha dub\noa are to ha found In tha rooms of any social\norganization In tha world\u2014 and learning besides\nthere als& In order to bo n member of tha Cos\nmos dub you must have something besides\nmoney and social standing It is probable that\nthere aro many members of other organisations\nin Washington who would be willing to throw\ntheir memberships into tho deep sea if the net\nwould buy for them admittance into the dub\n-of these adentlata\nThe headquarters of the Coamoa dnb are In\ntho old \"Dolly Madison\" residence It was there\nthat tho widow of President Madison lived and\nheld social away for years after the death of her\nhusband During the Civil war for a time Admi\nral Wilkes lived In tha Madison house It was\nWilkes who took Mason and Slidell from the Brit-\ntab steamer \"Trent\" and thereby nearly brought\non war between tho United States sad Great\nBritain at a time when such n war might have\nInsured ultimate victory to tho Confederate arms\nThe biological survey of the United States -government\nhas lost the services of Dr C Hart\nMerrlam who for years waa tho surrey's chief\nand who In tba early dps worked so hard to\nsnake theservb what he succeeded in nuking It\none of tho most useful departments of govern\nment Dr Merrlam has accepted the direction of\nthe Hardman Foundation for Zoological Re\nmarch Mrs Hardman tho widow of E H Har\nriman tho great financier and railroad man has\ncarried out tho wishes of her husband and has\not said n largo sum of money to bo used for\ngmrposea of aoologlcal study Acting nu question\nably in line with her husband's wishes Mrs Har\nliman requested Dr Merrlam to taka charge of\nthe work\nIt is probable that tho former chief of tho bio\nlogical survey is the foremost authority in tho\nUnited States in matters pertaining to certain\nlines of natural history work It waa Dr Mer\nxiam mors than any other man to whom Theo\ndore Roosevelt went for advice abont the aeopc\n-of his expected work In Africa The doctor and\nthe -colonel have been friends sines boyhood -when\nin New York state both were punning bird\natudlea and exchanging let ten on general sub\nJeete of natural history\nThose words about Dr Merrlam and tba Har-\niriman Zoological Foundation lead one to tell a\nstory about tho into financier which perhaps\nWill throw some light on a aide of hla life con\ncerning which most people probably know little\nOm year ago last winter I want south from\n1 \"Washington bound tor Augusta Go with a\nIrlend E H Harritnan's private car waa at\ntached to the tnln at one of the stations on tha\nway R happened that my friend was a close per\nsonal acquaintance of Mr Hnrriman and he was\nInvited to dine with the thunder on hla private\ncar and waa told to bring hla friond with him\nprovided the friend would like to come\nThen were several men of largo affairs at\n-that lltllo dinner party one of the guests being\nthe president of one of tho gras test railroad\n-systems In tha world Tha conversation natu\nrally waa about Mg affairs of the financial world\nconcerning which 1 knew very little and 1 am\nfree to confess ecred much less After hearing\na good deal about certain things concerning\nwhich tha discussion was more or lees unlntelll\nglbte to me 1 ventured to break Into tho conver\nsation and to tall Mr Harrlman that 1 had such\nof the Journals of tho \"Harrlman Alaska Expedi\ntion\" an already had been published and more\nover that 1 had read them\nFor the next two houre I hod ample evidence\nthat B H Harrlman cared for something besides\nrailroads Ten or twelve years before ho had\nEARTHQUAKES IN ARIZONA\nPeople Plad From Territory Fifty\nMilts Square Because of Rumblings\nIncreasing In Magnitude\nFlagstaff Aria\u2014 A territory 60 miles\nsquare and extending from hero to\ntho Grand Canyon of tho Colorado\nriver stands practically depopulated\nbecause of earthquakes and rumblings\nwhich arc steadily increasing In mag\nnitude and violence\nIndiana of whom there were many\nin the region fled when the quakes\noccurred terrified by sinister imports\nwhich they imagined to ho contained\nIn tho cracking -of tho solid ground\nTribal tales of tho ancient activities\nnow burned out craters of which\nthere an more than 60 in tho region\nhastened their flight The whites re\nmained until their houses fell about\nthem\nJ 3 Chaves the first ok the refu\ngees to reach Flagstaff reported that\nhla house had cracked open Others\nwho arrived Inter reported that vd\ncanlo stones weighing many tons had\nbeen tom from their beds and sent\ncrashing down tho mountain sides and\nthat tho whole district was in n state\nof unreat\nTho whole district la of tho volcanic\norigin Present phenomena are at\ntributed to a flipping of tho earth\u2019s\nCroat\nWALL OF BUILDING FELL IN\nExcavation for Projected Skyscraper\non Let Next to Bank Caused Side\nof House To Sink\nRichmond Va\u2014 The east wan of\nthe First National Bank building\nbom top to bottom for n distance of\n15 to S5 foot from the front sack into\nthe excavation for n projected sky\nscraper at teat point\nWith It went the eutennoat of the\nfour columns on tho front of the build\ning which facet southward on Main\nstreet This fell acroca the car tracks\non Main street narrowly milling an\napproaching car\nAlmost miraculously nobody was in\njured by the collapse of tho wan so\nfar as can be ascertained Tho bank\nis moving to another building The\nloss is several thousand dollars\nTRAIN STRUCK TAXICAB\nPoughkeepsie STYr-A taxicab con\ntaining Edward S Atwater and George\nCornwell prominent residents of this\ncity waa struck by a train of the New\nEngland railroad at n private crossing\nnorth of this city\nTho two passengers and the chauf\nfeur George Key wen injured so se\nriously that onp died Instantly and\nthe others are dying Atwater has\nfractured skull and n broken leg\nCornwell who is dead waa vice pres\nident and trustee of the Poughkeepsie\nSavings bank Atwater la n wealthy\nbanker and president of tho Farmers'\nand Manufacturers\u2019 bank of tela city\nTHE MARKETS\nCincinnati Live Stock\nCattle\u2014 Shippers f550BG50 butcher\nsteers extra 9595at10 good to choice\nS475a575 heifers extra 9475S5 good\nto choice 94a465 cows extra 9450\n1485 good to choice 93A5S4A5 Bulla\nBolognas 94a4S5 fat bulla 9450a\n95 Calves\u2014 Extra 1925 fair to good\n97-50a9 Hogs Heavy 99a915\nxrd to choice packers and butchers\n99Z5a930 mixed packers 9915a9S0\ncommon to heavy fat sows 982Sa835\nlight shippers 9 Oat35 pigs (110 lbs\nand leas 36a875 Sheep\u2014 Extra 94\ngood to choice 9325a390 Lambs\u2014\nExtra 97 good to choice 96a885 year\nlings 94a5\nCincinnati Grain\nWheat\u2014 No S red 9101 al 04 No I\nred 93a97c Corn\u2014 No I white 67a\n57Kc No I white MKa57c No I yel\nlow SSaSGc No